Remarks.
This species was described after 1 male and 1 female without type designation (
Stål 1875
). The male was subsequently labelled as “typus” and the female as “allotypus” in the NHRS. Because of the improbability of holotype I gave the only male in the NHRS as lectotype which is the first indication of the type designation (
Ünal 2011: 14
) for this species. Therefore, I confirm here again the male labelled as “typus” in the NHRS is the lectotype and the female labelled as “allotypus” in the NHRS is paralectotype of this species.
